ID Key, Motion, and Order to Seal

Defendant is in custody with appearance of Ms. Craker. Anne Terrien appears with the State of Wisconsin. Court will amend the complaint with updated address. State makes request of $5000 cash with conditions of no contact with victim 1 no use or  possession of any controlled substances or drug related paraphernalia without a vaild prescription. There are no prior criminal convictions in Wisconsin or Minnesota. The request is based of the seriousness of the offenses listed on the probable cause statement. Court inquires on the level offenses on the probable cause. State asserts it is 2nd sexual assult, class C felony, false imprisonment, class H, possession with intent to deliver cocaine, class E felony, possession of narcotic drugs, class I. Court inquires when State was looking to set initial appearance. State is looking at Monday, January 24th if the Court is agreeable otherwise, Friday, January 21st. 
Craker asserts defendant does have some cash he can post. Atty Craker doesn't believe that $5000 is necessary. As the State noted, there is no prior criminal history or missed appearances. Defendant does have 4 children in the area and does have local ties to the community. Atty Craker asserts defendant is set to join the Electricians Union on Feb 22nd. He does have the ability to contribute to society and the community. Atty Craker states defendant can post maybe a few thousand dollars. 
Court has concerns of the charges against defendant. Court Orders $5000 with conditions of no contact with victim 1 as listed in ID Key, no use or possession of any controlled substances or drug related paraphernalia without a vaild prescription. 
Atty Craker asserts defendant does not currently qualify.
